## üîß Issues Found & Fixes

### ‚úÖ **Issue 1: TypeScript Path Aliases Not Recognized**

**Problem:** TypeScript couldn't resolve module imports using path aliases like `@shared/ui/Button/Button`.

**Error:**
```
Cannot find module '@shared/ui/Button/Button' or its corresponding type declarations.
```

**Root Cause:** 
- Vite had path aliases configured in [vite.config.ts](file:///c:/Projects/Finance-Tracker-fe/vite.config.ts) for bundling
- TypeScript config ([tsconfig.app.json](file:///c:/Projects/Finance-Tracker-fe/tsconfig.app.json)) was missing the `paths` mapping
- TypeScript uses its own configuration for type checking, separate from Vite

**Fix Applied:**
Added the `paths` configuration to [tsconfig.app.json](file:///c:/Projects/Finance-Tracker-fe/tsconfig.app.json):

```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    // ... other options
    "paths": {
      "@app/*": ["./src/app/*"],
      "@pages/*": ["./src/pages/*"],
      "@widgets/*": ["./src/widgets/*"],
      "@features/*": ["./src/features/*"],
      "@entities/*": ["./src/entities/*"],
      "@shared/*": ["./src/shared/*"]
    }
  }
}
```

> [!NOTE]
> We intentionally did NOT add `baseUrl: "."` as it's deprecated in TypeScript 7.0. With `moduleResolution: "bundler"`, TypeScript resolves paths relative to the tsconfig location automatically.

**Result:** ‚úÖ TypeScript now correctly resolves all FSD layer imports!

