## üßí How Your App Works (Explained Simply)

Think of your Finance Tracker app like a **restaurant kitchen**:

### üè† **1. The Restaurant (index.html)**
This is the main building where customers enter. It has:
- A **front door** (the HTML page)
- A **dining area** (the `<div id="root"></div>`)
- A **kitchen entrance** (the `<script>` tag that calls [main.tsx](file:///c:/Projects/Finance-Tracker-fe/src/main.tsx))

### üö™ **2. The Kitchen Entrance (main.tsx)**
This is where the magic starts! It's like the head chef preparing everything:
- Gets the **dining area** (`root` div)
- Calls the **main chef** (App component)
- Makes sure everything is **fresh and safe** (StrictMode)

### üë®‚Äçüç≥ **3. The Head Chef (App.tsx)**
This is your main App component. The head chef:
- Uses a **recipe book** (StoreProvider - Redux store)
- Arranges the **dishes** (your UI components)
- Makes the **plate look pretty** (Tailwind CSS classes)

### üì¶ **4. The Ingredient Storage (Redux Store)**
This is like a big refrigerator that:
- **Stores ingredients** (your app's data)
- **Remembers what you bought** (state management)
- **Shares ingredients** with all chefs (components can access data)

### üé® **5. The Plate Decorations (Button Component)**
These are reusable decorations:
- **Pre-made garnishes** (Button component)
- Can be **customized** (primary, secondary, danger variants)
- **Looks consistent** (same style everywhere)

